The paper discusses the development of a new gradient estimator for importance-sampled objectives in deep latent variable models. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the estimator on generative and structured output prediction models, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of discrete latent variables, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
